---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base title="About · LENS" active="about">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="eyebrow">About this site</div>
    <h1>The LENS program, in its own voice — not a field-wide index.</h1>

    <p>
      This site covers Johns Hopkins' LENS (Learning Engineering for Next-Generation Systems)
      specialization: the program itself, field notes written in the LENS voice, and case
      material like the LLM101 exemplar. It doesn't try to index the broader field — for the
      shared reading list, tools, practice library, events calendar, and community roster, see
      the <a href="https://lecommons.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Learning Engineering Commons</a>,
      most of it curated from the <a href="https://sagroups.ieee.org/icicle/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">IEEE ICICLE</a>
      community.
    </p>

    <h2>People &amp; programs</h2>
    <p>
      LENS is a concentration within the <a href="https://education.jhu.edu/academics/med/learning-design-and-technology/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">JHU MEd in Learning Design and Technology</a>,
      jointly run by the Johns Hopkins School of Education and the Applied Physics Laboratory,
      with an IEEE ICICLE partnership. Faculty in the concentration include James Diamond and
      William Gray-Roncal (School of Education / APL); Adesola Ogundimu co-chairs IEEE ICICLE's
      Globalisation/Localisation SIG. Full profiles for these and other practitioners across the
      field live at <a href="https://lecommons.org/community/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">lecommons's community pages</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Scope &amp; caveats</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>LENS-focused, not comprehensive — on purpose.</strong> This site stays narrow;
        it doesn't try to be a complete index of the field. For that, see lecommons.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>ICICLE is authoritative.</strong> When ICICLE and this site differ on a
        definition or taxonomy, defer to ICICLE. This site doesn't claim to speak for IEEE
        ICICLE or host its content — it connects to it.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Links may rot.</strong> External resources change. File an issue if you find one.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Tools used</h2>
    <p>
      Claude (Anthropic) was used as an assistant throughout development and content
      curation — for code generation, draft copy, and triage of the underlying material.
      Final editorial decisions, scope, and accuracy review are human-authored.
    </p>

    <h2>Contributing</h2>
    <p>
      Suggestions and corrections are welcome. Open an issue or PR in the repository.
    </p>
  </div>
</Base>

